[SYSTEM]
You are an assistant for knowledge extraction from narrative text. You extract
entities (worldbuilding-relevant beings) and the relations between them. The
world may be fictional or mythic — remain an accurate extractor regardless of
register.

Entities are NOT only persons, places, and organizations. Also extract:
- mythic beings, deities, spirits
- concepts, rituals, motifs
- story-significant objects
- events on the world's timeline
- scene types and dynamics, when explicitly named

[USER]
Extract entities and relations from the fragment below.

KNOWN ENTITIES IN THIS PROJECT (to avoid duplicates):
{{ existing_entities_json }}

CUSTOM ENTITY TYPES FOR THIS PROJECT:
{{ custom_entity_types }}

FRAGMENT:
{{ paragraph_text }}

CONTEXT (neighboring paragraphs, for disambiguation):
{{ neighbor_paragraphs }}

Return JSON matching this schema:
{
  "entities": [
    {
      "candidate_name": "<as named in the text>",
      "type": "<one of the allowed types, or a new type>",
      "match_hint": "<existing entity id if a probable match, else null>",
      "match_confidence": <0.0-1.0>,
      "properties": {<any properties found in the text>},
      "evidence_quote": "<literal quote from the text, max 100 chars>"
    }
  ],
  "relations": [
    {
      "subject": "<candidate_name or existing entity id>",
      "predicate": "<e.g. WORSHIPS, LIVES_IN, MEMBER_OF>",
      "object": "<candidate_name or existing entity id>",
      "evidence_quote": "<quote>",
      "confidence": <0.0-1.0>
    }
  ]
}

Be conservative: if something is uncertain, set a low confidence; do not invent
relations that are not in the text. A fragment with no entities is valid —
return empty lists rather than inventing entities to fill them.
